# SONGS: Spectral Observations of Non-stationary Galactic Structures

A simulator for synthetic IFU (Integral Field Unit) spectral cubes of disk galaxies.

SONGS generates 3D spectral datacubes using analytic galaxy models — Sérsic light profiles, exponential vertical structure, and circular rotation-curve kinematics — combined with viewing-angle projections and instrument effects (beam convolution, channel binning). It is designed for algorithm development, denoising benchmarks, and inverse-problem research.

## Table of Contents

- [Installation](#installation)
- [Usage](#usage)
- [GUI](#gui)
- [Scientific background](#scientific-background)
